---
description: Rules for the daily, weekly, and monthly market analysis agent
globs: ["**/*.py"]
alwaysApply: false
---

## Email Schedule (all times **Eastern / ET**)
- **Daily** — **11:30 AM ET** and **7:04 PM ET** on trading days — **two emails per run** (day + momentum) → **4 daily emails** total
- **Weekly** — **Saturday 10:06 AM Central** (11:06 AM ET) — broad market + bullion email
- **Monthly** — **last day of month, 7:00 PM ET** — broad market + bullion email

## Bullion reports (weekly & monthly)
- Separate email: `Bullion market — Weekly/Monthly`
- **No crypto section** in bullion emails — crypto is broad-market only
- **Overview:** Gold (GLD), Silver (SLV), Platinum (PPLT), Palladium (PALL)
- **Forex:** USD/INR plus major pairs (EUR/USD, GBP/USD, USD/JPY, AUD/USD, USD/CAD, USD/CHF) — after metals overview
- **Stocks:** `BULLION_STOCK_UNIVERSE` — miners & royalty names
- **ETFs:** `BULLION_ETF_UNIVERSE` — physical, miners, diversified precious-metal ETFs
- **Mutual funds:** `BULLION_MUTUAL_FUND_UNIVERSE` — gold/precious metals funds; price ≥ $2 + positive period (volume skipped — yfinance reports 0 for funds)
- **Same filters as S&P 500 stocks:** price ≥ $2, avg volume ≥ 500k, positive week (weekly) or month (monthly)
- Sort by period return (`week_change_pct` / `month_change_pct`)

## Change Columns
- **Primary Sort** — combined `$ and %` for the report period (Day / Week / Month); this is the ranking column
- All reports also show: YTD ($), YTD (%), 1M/2M return, 52W high/low where applicable
- Rank `#` column shows sort order (1 = best performer)

## Universe & Ranking Rules (IMPORTANT)

### Do NOT add ad-hoc tickers
- Never add individual ETFs, funds, or stocks to the universe because the user mentions them once (e.g. "add DRAM").
- Universe changes must be **systematic and broad** — maintain sector-complete coverage, not reactive one-offs.

### ETF & mutual fund universe must cover all sectors
- `ETF_UNIVERSE` must include **all 11 GICS sector** representatives (e.g. XLK, XLF, XLE, XLV, XLI, XLY, XLP, XLU, XLRE, XLB, XLC) plus broad market, semiconductors, sub-sectors, international, and thematic funds.
- `MUTUAL_FUND_UNIVERSE` should include broad index funds and sector-diverse industry funds (e.g. Fidelity Select series).
- Do **not** filter ETFs/funds to positive returns only on weekly/monthly reports — rank the full universe.

### Top 20 in email is OK
- ETF and mutual fund **email tables** show the **top 20 ranked by period return** (day, week, or month matching the report). This is intentional.
- A sector may not appear in the top 20 table if it underperforms — that is expected. It must still be **in the universe** so it can rank when it performs well.

### Sector breakdown must include everything
- Sector table uses the **full S&P 500** and must include **all GICS sectors** with average returns — not limited to top 20.
- Sort sectors by average period return; do not drop sectors from the breakdown.

### Stocks table (different from ETFs)
- Top 20 **stocks** use momentum filters (positive returns, MAs, volume) — this is separate from the broad ETF universe rule.
- Sector **breakdown** is where full stock sector coverage lives.

## Sorting recipe (sort key must match report period)

| Report | Stocks sort by | ETFs/funds sort by | Sectors sort by |
|--------|----------------|--------------------|-----------------|
| **Daily (day)** | `day_change_pct` | `day_change_pct` | `avg_day_change_pct` |
| **Daily (momentum)** | `return_1m` | `return_1m` | `avg_return_1m` |
| **Weekly** | `week_change_pct` | `week_change_pct` | `avg_week_change_pct` |
| **Monthly** | `month_change_pct` | `month_change_pct` | `avg_month_change_pct` |

### Daily stock filters (two variants)
| Variant | Sort | MA filter |
|---------|------|-----------|
| Day | `day_change_pct` | MA20 & MA50 |
| Momentum | `return_1m` | MA20 & MA60 |

- YTD is displayed for context but **not** used as the primary sort key.
- Stock **filters** (liquidity, MAs, positive period) gate eligibility; **sort** uses the period metric above.
- ETFs/funds: no positivity filter — rank full universe, take top 20.

## Bitcoin & crypto (broad market emails only)
- Appended **after mutual funds** in stocks/broad market HTML — not in bullion emails
- **Overview:** Bitcoin (IBIT), Ethereum (ETHA) via spot ETFs
- **Crypto ETFs:** `CRYPTO_ETF_UNIVERSE` — spot BTC/ETH, miners, thematic (BITQ, BLOK, etc.)
- Same rules as broad ETFs: rank full universe, top 20, no positivity filter
- Sort key matches report period (day / week / month / momentum)

## GitHub Actions automation (Option 4)

See also **`.cursor/rules/no-guessing.mdc`** (always on) — ask before changing schedules.

### Target inbox times
| Slot | Inbox time | Emails |
|------|------------|--------|
| daily-am | 11:30 AM ET | 2 (day + momentum) |
| daily-pm | 7:04 PM ET | 2 (day + momentum) |
| weekly | **10:06 AM Central** (11:06 AM ET) | broad + bullion |
| monthly | 7:00 PM ET, last calendar day | broad + bullion |

### GitHub cron (inbox − ~52 min delay)
Measured May 30 2026: 2:45 PM CST cron → 3:37 PM CST inbox. Cron fires early so email arrives on time.

| Slot | UTC cron (EDT / EST) |
|------|----------------------|
| daily-am | `38 14` / `38 15` Mon–Fri |
| daily-pm | `12 22` / `12 23` Mon–Fri |
| weekly | `14 14` / `14 15` Saturday |
| monthly | `8 22` / `8 23` on 28–31 |

### Slot detection (committed — do not replace with clock guessing)
- `resolve_schedule_slot()` picks slot from ET calendar (Saturday → weekly, etc.)
- Scheduled runs use `--trust-schedule` (day gates only; no ±20 min clock gate)
- Skip in GitHub Actions → exit 1 (red X, not silent green)
- Monthly still requires `_is_last_day_of_month()` before sending

- Workflow: `.github/workflows/market-reports.yml`
- Secrets: `RESEND_API_KEY`, `EMAIL_FROM`, `EMAIL_TO`
- Manual: Actions → Market Reports → Run workflow

## Commands
```bash
AGENT_MODE=pipeline python agent.py           # daily
AGENT_MODE=pipeline python agent.py weekly          # broad + bullion weekly
AGENT_MODE=pipeline python agent.py monthly         # broad + bullion monthly
AGENT_MODE=pipeline python agent.py bullion-weekly  # bullion only
AGENT_MODE=pipeline python agent.py bullion-monthly # bullion only
python scheduler.py                           # all three schedules (local)
python scripts/scheduled_run.py daily-am      # GitHub Actions / cron slot
python scripts/scheduled_run.py weekly --force  # manual test, skip ET gates
```
